        "text": "By the late 1940s, the favorite past-time of faculty and graduate students in Fine Hall at Princeton University was board games, including the famous Go and Chess, as well as the less famous Kriegspiel. During this time, ‘beautiful mind’ John Forbes Nash Jr (1928-2015) invented his own game, “Nash”, later marketed by the Parker Bros under the name “Hex”. This essay tells the story of its discovery.\n\nPrinceton University (1948–51)"
